================================================================================
                    LOGGING - COMPLETE NOTES WITH DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

1. LOGGING KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
--------------------------------
Definition: Logging ek process hai jisme application apne execution ke dauraan
jo bhi kaam karti hai (Events, Errors, Warnings), uski jaankari ko ek specific
format mein record karti hai (Console ya File mein).

Simple Words: Application ki **Diary** likhna.

2. LOGGER KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
-------------------------------
Definition: Logger ek object hai jo application ke code mein log messages ko
likhne (publish) ke liye use hota hai. Ye SLF4J ya Log4j jaise frameworks se aata hai.

Example: `private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyClass.class);`

3. LOG LEVEL KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
----------------------------------
Definition: Log Level ek tag/value hoti hai jo batati hai ki current log message
kitna important hai. Isi ke hisaab se decide hota hai ki log message ko print
karna hai ya ignore karna hai (Filtering).

Levels (Severity ke hisaab se ascending):
- **TRACE** : Sabse zyada detailed info (Har line ka execution). Development ke liye.
- **DEBUG** : Variables ki values, Method entry/exit. Debugging ke liye.
- **INFO**  : Normal application flow (e.g., "User Login Successful"). Production Default.
- **WARN**  : Potential issue (e.g., "Memory usage is high"). Future error ka indication.
- **ERROR** : Actual failure (e.g., "Database Connection Lost"). Action required.

4. APPENDER KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
---------------------------------
Definition: Appender ek component hai jo decide karta hai ki **Logs kahan bheje jayenge**.
Ye Destination set karta hai.

Types of Appenders:
- **ConsoleAppender** : Logs ko Command Line / Terminal / IDE Console mein print karta hai.
- **FileAppender**   : Logs ko ek specific file mein likhta hai (e.g., `app.log`).
- **RollingFileAppender** : Jab file size badi ho jaye ya din badle, toh purani file archive
                    kar deta hai aur nayi file bana deta hai.

5. LAYOUT / PATTERN KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
-----------------------------------------
Definition: Pattern batata hai ki **Log Line ka Format kaisa dikhega**.
Jaise ki time pehle aaye, level baad mein aaye.

Example Pattern: `%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss} [%thread] %-5level %logger{36} - %msg%n`
- `%d` : Date & Time
- `%thread` : Thread Name (e.g., http-nio-8080-exec-1)
- `%level` : INFO/ERROR/WARN
- `%logger` : Class name jisne log kiya
- `%msg` : Actual message tumne jo likha
- `%n` : New Line (Enter)

6. SLF4J KYA HAI? (DEFINITION)
------------------------------
Definition: Simple Logging Facade for Java (SLF4J) ek **Abstraction Layer** hai.
Ye sirf Interface provide karta hai. Actual implementation tum Logback ya Log4j2 se karte ho.
Fayda: Bina code change kiye tum log library badal sakte ho.

7. LOGBACK vs LOG4J2 (DIFFERENCE)
---------------------------------
- **Logback** : Spring Boot ka Default. XML based config. General purpose ke liye best.
- **Log4j2**  : High performance, Async logging support better hai. Agar bohot zyada traffic hai toh ye use karo.

8. MDC (MAPPED DIAGNOSTIC CONTEXT) - DEFINITION
-----------------------------------------------
Definition: MDC ek **Thread-Local Map** hai jisme tum custom key-value pairs daal sakte ho
(e.g., `userId`, `requestId`). Ye values automatically har log line ke saath print ho jaati hain,
jisse ek hi user ki saari requests ko filter karna aasan ho jata hai.

9. ROOT LOGGER KYA HAI?
-----------------------
Definition: Ye **Parent Logger** hai. Agar kisi specific class ke liye tumne level set nahi kiya,
toh ye Root Logger ki settings inherit kar leta hai. Isme tum Global Level aur Global Appenders set karte ho.

10. LOG ROTATION KYA HAI?
-------------------------
Definition: Log files ko manage karne ki technique. Agar ye na ho toh `app.log` 10GB ki ho jayegi.
Rotation automatically purani file ko `app.2026-04-01.log` rename kar deta hai ya delete kar deta hai.
- **TimeBasedRollingPolicy** : Har roz nayi file.
- **SizeBasedTriggeringPolicy** : 10MB hone par nayi file.


<configuration>
    <!-- ConsoleAppender -> Print on console  -->
    <appender name="Console" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">
        <encoder>
            <pattern>%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger{36} - %msg%n</pattern>
        </encoder>
    </appender>

    <!-- RollingFileAppender -> Create file name with app.log and all logs print in app.log file  -->
    <appender name="File" class="ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender">
        <file>logs/app.log</file>
        <rollingPolicy class="ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.TimeBasedRollingPolicy">
            <fileNamePattern>logs/app.%d{yyyy-MM-dd}.log</fileNamePattern>
            <maxHistory>30</maxHistory>
        </rollingPolicy>
        <encoder>
            <pattern>%d{yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger{36} - %msg%n</pattern>
        </encoder>
    </appender>

    <!-- Level what u want  -->
    <root level="INFO">
        <appender-ref ref="File" />
        <appender-ref ref="Console" />
    </root>

</configuration>